    "methodology": "Prison deaths data covers all deaths in prison custody in England and Wales, including natural causes, self-inflicted, and homicide. Self-inflicted deaths are classified by the PPO following investigation. Deaths following police contact are recorded by the IOPC and include deaths in or following police custody, pursuit-related deaths, road traffic fatalities involving police, and deaths following other police contact. Self-harm incidents count individual episodes, not individuals — one person may account for multiple incidents.",
